This tool is used to backup the database or file-system on client machine.
To use this tool, we need to install the dependency package firstly(Use centos as example):

1. Install system package
-------------------------------------------
| yum install -y python-pip               |    
| yum install -y gcc-c++.x86_64 gcc.x86_64|
| yum install -y python-devel             | 
------------------------------------------


2. Install python package  
---------------------------------
| pip install -r requirements.txt|
---------------------------------

To deploy this project, we need to use cron to set the daily task schedule,
3. Use crontab -e to fill in above content.
-------------------------------------------------
|0 1 * * * python $PROJECT_DIR/backup-agent.py   |
-------------------------------------------------
The $PROJECT_DIR is the tool location.

4. Finally, fill in the backup.conf for any database or file-system you want to backup.

5. Test whether the module can run normally manually
--------------------------------------
| python $PROJECT_DIR/backup-agent.py |
--------------------------------------

Any problem, please contact Mei Lei <meil@rc.inesa.com>

